    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-27T16:58:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-27T16:58:00-05:00" n="625"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d625">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Conference files, lot 60 D 627, <gloss
                        target="#t_CF1">CF</gloss> 242: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">United States Delegation</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d625fn1">Drafted by the Secretary of State.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-27T17:58:00-04:00"
                            >May 27, 1954—5:58 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Tedul1">Tedul</gloss> 135. No distribution. Eyes only Under
                    Secretary from Secretary. Your <gloss target="#t_Tedul1">Tedul</gloss> 127.<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d625fn2">Dated May 26, <ref target="#pg_935">p.
                        935</ref>.</note> Subject matter discussed with President who <pb
                        facs="0976" n="950" xml:id="pg_950"/> agrees yon should not by your
                    departure risk misinterpretation. I shall, therefore, plan Western trip on
                    assumption communications will be adequate. If not will interrupt and return
                    canceling out my speaking.</p>
                <p>I assume by time <persName corresp="#p_PH1">Phleger</persName> gets through his
                    case, Geneva will probably be over but if not and you need him, I will ask him
                    to return to Geneva.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
